00:00:14:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:14:030000.Dialogue: Last night, me wanting to try that stuff out of the Kama Sutra. Was that fun for you or kinda racially insensitive?

00:00:21:000000.Speaker: Priya
00:00:21:000000.Dialogue: Yes. Just because you're in bed with an India woman you think that gives you permission to use crazy positions from an ancient Indian love manual?

00:00:28:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:28:210000.Dialogue: Hey, if you can find a book called Weird Sex with White Boys I'd be okay with that.

00:00:35:150000.Speaker: Priya
00:00:35:150000.Dialogue: No, no, you know you have such beautiful eyes. Have you ever thought about getting contacts?

00:00:40:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:40:150000.Dialogue: I tried in the seventh grade. I could never get used to them.

00:00:44:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:44:180000.Dialogue: Yeah. If I had contacts, I would have been the coolest Debate Club president ever to be stuffed into his own cello case.

00:00:52:180000.Speaker: Priya
00:00:52:180000.Dialogue: If you had them on now, you could see what we're going to do next.

00:00:59:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:59:200000.Dialogue: That-That's okay. I can infer from context.

00:01:05:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:05:040000.Dialogue: Hey, Raj, you wanna see a new magic trick I been working on?

00:01:07:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:07:030000.Dialogue: Eh, Howard. If I may interject here with a piece of friendly advice. Is working on magic tricks, really how you want to spend your time? Uh, granted, you're just an engineer, but...

00:01:20:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:20:010000.Dialogue: that doesn't mean you might not someday build a geegaw or a thingamabob that that may get you a thank you in someone else's Nobel Prize acceptance speech.

00:01:34:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:34:040000.Dialogue: Is the trick making him disappear?

00:01:45:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:45:050000.Dialogue: Now spread them out on the table. Face down. Pick one. Look at it.

00:01:50:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:50:060000.Dialogue: Now remember your card. Put it back in the deck.

00:01:52:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:52:060000.Dialogue: Is it any wonder he doesn't have a doctorate?

00:01:56:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:56:090000.Dialogue: Now remind me, what's your birthday?

00:01:59:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:59:220000.Dialogue: Okay, October is the tenth month. So 10-- one plus zero is one plus six is seven. Turn over the seventh card.

00:02:18:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:18:060000.Dialogue: Oh it's not cool. It's a childish trick, designed to confuse and intrigue simpletons.

00:02:27:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:27:200000.Dialogue: A magician never reveals his secrets. But surely a future Nobel Prize winner can figure it out.

00:02:41:060000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:41:060000.Dialogue: You ever notice when he thinks real hard it smells like bacon?

00:02:57:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:57:220000.Dialogue: Check it out. I just got contacts.

00:03:29:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:29:210000.Dialogue: One, two, three, four, five. No way.

00:03:36:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:36:010000.Dialogue: Seven of clubs! That is amazing!

00:03:43:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:43:210000.Dialogue: All magic tricks are merely a combination of manipulation and misdirection with the occasional dwarf in a box wiggling his feet.

00:03:53:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:53:030000.Dialogue: Oh, really? So how did I do it?

00:03:55:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:55:050000.Dialogue: I don't care how you did it. I have more important things to think about.

00:04:07:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:07:110000.Dialogue: I thought you had more important things to think about.

00:04:09:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:09:200000.Dialogue: I do. You just happened to have caught me on a break.

00:04:14:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:14:220000.Dialogue: Oh, let me see those cards.

00:04:18:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:18:050000.Dialogue: Big deal. Not knowing is part of the fun.

00:04:21:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:21:020000.Dialogue: Not knowing is part of the fun. Was that the motto of your community college?

00:04:27:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:27:010000.Dialogue: Hey, guys, what do you think? Priya took me clothes shopping.

00:04:30:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:30:210000.Dialogue: Hey, you look great. Good for you, Priya. I could never get that stupid hoodie off him when we were... Well, you look great.

00:04:43:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:43:130000.Dialogue: New contacts. I should have done this years ago.

00:04:49:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:49:160000.Dialogue: So you finally getting used to them doing it on a daily basis?

00:04:52:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:52:230000.Dialogue: I'm not going out with him. He can sleep with whoever he wants.

00:04:55:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:55:140000.Dialogue: Yeah, I was talking to Raj.

00:05:04:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:04:200000.Dialogue: This deck is rigged in some fashion.

00:05:06:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:06:090000.Dialogue: Fine. Get another deck and I'll do the trick with that.

00:05:08:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:08:160000.Dialogue: So you're saying this is a regulation deck?

00:05:10:070000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:10:070000.Dialogue: I'm saying believe in magic, you muggle.

00:05:16:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:16:170000.Dialogue: You know, well, I'm happy Leonard's found someone.

00:05:28:200000.Speaker: Priya
00:05:28:200000.Dialogue: How many Star Trek uniforms do you have?

00:05:36:070000.Speaker: Priya
00:05:36:070000.Dialogue: Uh-huh. Listen, we need to talk about something.

00:05:41:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:41:030000.Dialogue: Oh, my God, you're breaking up with me!

00:05:44:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:44:020000.Dialogue: Why would you take me out shopping and then break up with me? That is so cruel!

00:05:47:230000.Speaker: Priya
00:05:47:230000.Dialogue: Leonard, I'm not breaking up with you.

00:05:58:160000.Speaker: Priya
00:05:58:160000.Dialogue: It's a little weird, your ex-girlfriend hanging out here all the time.

00:06:04:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:04:040000.Dialogue: I know. I usually never see my ex-girlfriends, unless their hard drives crash.

00:06:09:070000.Speaker: Priya
00:06:09:070000.Dialogue: I'm just saying, how would you feel if I was hanging out with my ex-boyfriend?

00:06:15:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:15:030000.Dialogue: Um, not great, I guess. But Penny and I are just friends.

00:06:18:100000.Speaker: Priya
00:06:18:100000.Dialogue: I don't care. This is a woman you have slept with. If you want her around, then I have to wonder if maybe you're not ready to move on.

00:06:26:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:26:090000.Dialogue: No, no-no-no, I'm ready! I gave up the gift of sight for you. If that's not moving on, what is?

00:06:32:050000.Speaker: Priya
00:06:32:050000.Dialogue: You need to cut the cord with Penny.

00:06:40:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:40:050000.Dialogue: No, no, I'm confident. Its not like I'm unfamiliar with the get lost conversation. Although, this will be the first time I'll be the one saying it.

00:06:50:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:50:210000.Dialogue: Sure. Oh, God, you smell so good. Of course, that could just be my other senses getting stronger.

00:07:01:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:01:150000.Dialogue: Hypothetically, if I had access to a Lieutenant Uhura uniform, would you wear it?

00:07:10:060000.Speaker: Priya
00:07:10:060000.Dialogue: Leonard, it is a source of great pain to me and my family that my brother has that outfit in his wardrobe. Can we not discuss it?

00:07:24:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:24:040000.Dialogue: And was your card the jack of diamonds?

00:07:33:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:33:160000.Dialogue: Know how he did it yet?

00:07:41:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:41:140000.Dialogue: Aw, he has the same look my little nephew gets when he can't figure out how I got his nose.

00:07:50:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:50:220000.Dialogue: You know, I have some remedial magic tricks that might be more your speed. Like, ooh, look!

00:08:01:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:01:060000.Dialogue: Hey, I think I know how you did the card trick.

00:08:04:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:04:050000.Dialogue: Oh, please, if I don't know, you don't know. That's axiomatic.

00:08:15:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:15:180000.Dialogue: Not too bad for someone who doesn't know what axiomatic means.

00:08:28:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:28:190000.Dialogue: Hey, you. What happened with the contacts?

00:08:31:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:31:160000.Dialogue: One of them's upstairs. The other one sort of slipped back into my skull.

00:08:36:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:36:120000.Dialogue: Hey, is that one of the new shirts Priya got you?

00:08:41:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:41:180000.Dialogue: No, that's silk. Seriously, what would you do without me?

00:08:49:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:49:140000.Dialogue: You know, I gotta tell you, I think you got a real winner with Priya.

00:08:54:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:54:020000.Dialogue: She seems really sweet. Believe me, you do not want to take that for granted. There are a lot of bitches out there.

00:09:04:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:04:200000.Dialogue: All right, I'll see you later.

00:09:06:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:06:160000.Dialogue: Uh, Penny, there's something I have to tell you.

00:09:10:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:10:120000.Dialogue: Okay, uh, how do I put this? Um... are you familiar with Darwin's observation of the finches in the Galapagos Islands?

00:09:21:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:21:010000.Dialogue: Did they make a movie about it?

00:09:26:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:26:230000.Dialogue: All right, well, anyway, Darwin observed that when two groups of finches competed over the same food source, eventually one of them would evolve a different beak shape so they could feed on something else.

00:09:41:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:41:160000.Dialogue: So what do you think we can learn from that behavior that we can apply to our own lives?

00:09:48:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:48:110000.Dialogue: Uh, a bird in the hand is worth two in the bush?

00:09:54:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:54:050000.Dialogue: Sure, that has birds in it.

00:09:59:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:59:100000.Dialogue: It's fun talking to you, Leonard; I always learn stuff.

00:10:05:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:05:200000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, but I'm gonna count that.

00:10:12:160000.Speaker: Priya
00:10:12:160000.Dialogue: Do you really have to wear that in bed?

00:10:19:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:19:040000.Dialogue: Yeah. The doctor didn't want me to rub my eye during the night. It was either this or one of those giant neck cones.

00:10:26:010000.Speaker: Priya
00:10:26:010000.Dialogue: So did you get to talk to Penny?

00:10:35:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:35:200000.Dialogue: She completely understood everything I said. Case closed.

00:10:40:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:40:070000.Dialogue: Maybe, but that's not my problem. She's not my girlfriend, you are.

00:10:45:130000.Speaker: Priya
00:10:45:130000.Dialogue: I hope you weren't cruel to her.

00:10:48:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:48:130000.Dialogue: Is the autumn cruel for letting the flowers die, or is that just nature's way?

00:11:03:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:03:110000.Dialogue: I think I figured out Wolowitz's magic trick,

00:11:06:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:06:050000.Dialogue: and I need you to pick a card.

00:11:10:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:10:220000.Dialogue: I am not opening that door, Sheldon!

00:11:20:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:20:080000.Dialogue: Pick a card, put it back, and prepare to be amazed.

00:11:57:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:57:060000.Dialogue: Now look at it, and put it back in the deck.

00:12:03:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:03:030000.Dialogue: Now do you remember your card? Of course I do, I have an eidetic memory. My apologies. Now shuffle the cards. Shuffling. Wait here.

00:12:22:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:22:120000.Dialogue: I'm reverse engineering Wolowitz's magic trick.

00:12:25:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:25:130000.Dialogue: What's up with the infrared cameras?

00:12:29:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:29:150000.Dialogue: I'm measuring residual heat levels on the playing cards to determine which one's been touched. By the way, if you hope to have children, I suggest you switch from briefs to boxers. Your testicles look a tad warm.

00:12:48:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:48:160000.Dialogue: Holy crap, are you connected to the Oak Ridge National Laboratory?

00:12:53:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:53:200000.Dialogue: Yes. I'm using their Cray supercomputer to analyze shuffling patterns.

00:12:57:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:57:170000.Dialogue: Sheldon, that computer is used for national defense. Hacking into it is a federal crime.

00:13:03:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:03:140000.Dialogue: Relax, we're not under attack right now.

00:13:06:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:06:180000.Dialogue: Okay, I'm leaving before the black helicopters get here.

00:13:13:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:13:130000.Dialogue: And is this my card? Rats!

00:13:22:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:22:080000.Dialogue: I wonder if Howard used a radioactive tracer. Where am I going to find uranium-235 this time of night? Come on, CraigsList.

00:13:39:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:39:030000.Dialogue: Is it racist that I took you to an Indian restaurant?

00:13:42:030000.Speaker: Priya
00:13:42:030000.Dialogue: It's okay, I like Indian food.

00:13:45:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:45:150000.Dialogue: Or as you probably call it back home, food.

00:13:49:020000.Speaker: Priya
00:13:49:020000.Dialogue: Why didn't you wear your contacts? Don't you like them?

00:13:53:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:53:080000.Dialogue: No, no, I do. It's just I knew I was having curry tonight and I only want one part of my body to burn at a time.

00:14:02:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:02:010000.Dialogue: You know... ...my company offered me a position here in Los Angeles.

00:14:07:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:07:020000.Dialogue: Does that mean you'd relocate here permanently?

00:14:27:190000.Speaker: Priya
00:14:27:190000.Dialogue: You did talk to her, didn't you?

00:14:28:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:28:230000.Dialogue: Of course, I did. I talked and talked and talked.

00:14:32:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:32:160000.Dialogue: Hey! Look at Leonard in his fancy-ass grownup clothes.

00:14:38:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:38:020000.Dialogue: Way to go, Priya. For once, he doesn't look like a mannequin in the boys' department.

00:14:44:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:44:030000.Dialogue: Hey, did he tell you I saved the silk shirt?

00:14:48:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:48:140000.Dialogue: He was gonna throw it in the washing machine with his Spiderman underwear.

00:14:58:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:58:030000.Dialogue: So how's the food here? Oh, wow, that is really, really good. Oh, I'm sorry. You guys are on a date. We can hang out anytime. Have fun.

00:15:09:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:09:220000.Dialogue: Oh, that's, hot, hot, hot, hot!

00:15:14:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:14:050000.Dialogue: Whoo! It really sneaks up on ya, huh? All right, I gotta go.

00:15:28:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:28:060000.Dialogue: Oh, I've been meaning to tell you, I figured out your magic trick.

00:15:34:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:34:100000.Dialogue: Oh, yes. In fact, I improved upon it.

00:15:38:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:38:170000.Dialogue: I'd love to see that. How about you, Raj?

00:15:41:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:41:080000.Dialogue: Beefaroni and a show? How do you turn that down?

00:16:05:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:05:150000.Dialogue: What's with the wand and the beep?

00:16:08:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:08:230000.Dialogue: The wand is called showmanship, and the beep is none of your business.

00:16:15:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:15:060000.Dialogue: Oh! Excuse me. I'm getting a text message completely unrelated to this magic trick. Oh, look, my dry cleaning's ready. And your card was the five of spades. Ta-da.

00:16:27:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:27:230000.Dialogue: These cards have barcodes on them. The wand is a reader. It's transmitting to your phone.

00:16:41:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:41:150000.Dialogue: That's pathetic. Let me show you how a real magician does it. Raj, take a card. Don't let me see it.

00:16:53:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:16:53:160000.Dialogue: Son of a gun, you're blowing my mind!

00:17:04:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:04:070000.Dialogue: That does it. I'm getting uranium.

00:17:13:120000.Speaker: Howard
00:17:13:120000.Dialogue: Maybe. When it stops being fun.

00:17:26:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:26:230000.Dialogue: Oh, hey, I was just on my way to work.

00:17:28:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:28:190000.Dialogue: Oh, okay, its not important. It can wait.

00:17:31:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:31:060000.Dialogue: No, it's all right. Walk me down. So, what's up?

00:17:33:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:33:210000.Dialogue: Uh, I kind of have a problem I was hoping you could help me with.

00:17:42:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:42:120000.Dialogue: Not far. Hey, if you ever wanna start a family, La Cañada has some great schools.

00:17:47:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:47:180000.Dialogue: Okay, I'm not moving anywhere. What the hell is this all about?

00:17:51:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:17:51:070000.Dialogue: Why does it have to be about anything? Can't a fella ask his buddy to relocate, no questions asked?

00:17:58:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:58:020000.Dialogue: Oh, for God's sake, Leonard, this is about Priya, isn't it? She doesn't want me hanging out with you.

00:18:07:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:07:020000.Dialogue: Okay, look. I happen to like your girlfriend.

00:18:14:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:14:040000.Dialogue: It doesn't matter. Look, I promise from now on I will keep my distance from you.

00:18:17:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:17:130000.Dialogue: Well, now, hold on. What kind of distance are we talking about? Because we are neighbors. I mean, I can hear the toilet flush in your apartment.

00:18:24:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:24:050000.Dialogue: You can hear my toilet flush?

00:18:26:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:26:200000.Dialogue: I don't listen for it, but it's nice to know everything's okay with your plumbing.

00:18:34:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:34:200000.Dialogue: Leonard, I get it. You're in a new relationship now. And I'm happy for you. So why don't we just shake hands and part friends?

00:18:41:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:41:050000.Dialogue: Well, now hold on. How about this? How about we still hang out, but on the down-low?

00:18:46:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:46:200000.Dialogue: Are you really that kind of guy?

00:18:50:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:50:090000.Dialogue: No. I actually felt kinda silly just saying on the down-low.

00:19:29:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:29:220000.Dialogue: Apparently, you can't hack into a government supercomputer and then try to buy uranium without the Department of Homeland Security tattling to your mother.

00:19:44:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:19:44:080000.Dialogue: Oh, that's too bad. Figure out the magic trick yet?

00:19:47:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:47:060000.Dialogue: Figure out the magic trick yet?

00:19:49:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:19:49:130000.Dialogue: Want me to tell you how to do it?

00:19:52:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:19:52:150000.Dialogue: I'll show you one more time. Raj?

00:19:55:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:55:230000.Dialogue: Hang on. This time do it with me, so I can make sure there's no monkey business.

00:20:28:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:20:28:220000.Dialogue: Yeah, he's gonna win the Nobel Prize.
